
| Principle | Full Form                       | Purpose                                     |
| --------- | ------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| **S**     | Single Responsibility Principle | One class â†’ one job                         |
| **O**     | Open/Closed Principle           | Open for extension, closed for modification |
| **L**     | Liskov Substitution Principle   | Child class should behave like parent       |
| **I**     | Interface Segregation Principle | No forced implementation of unused methods  |
| **D**     | Dependency Inversion Principle  | Depend on abstractions, not concretions     |

Single Responsibility Principle (SRP)